    "For each l-th layer, R l is initialised as the identity matrix and gradually learns to decorrelate the layer inputs during training, using its own, separate, learning rate and optimization scheme, usually vanilla stochastic gradient descent (SGD).",
    "This is done in parallel to minimizing the backpropagation (BP) loss during training.",
    "In its simplest implementation, R l is a square matrix, preserving the dimensionality of the input.",
    "After each mini-batch, R l is updated as follows:",
    "where η is a small, constant, and tunable learning rate, and C l captures the off-diagonal correlations of the layer inputs."
